A firm has embarked on a project to deliver clean water to thousands of residents. Embu Water and Sanitation Company (Ewasco) has received a Sh2.2 billion grant from Japanese Government to fund expansion of its water treatment plant at Mukangu. ALSO READ:

Embu County to give free underwear to girls The project would increase supply of treated water to almost 70 per cent of the county to the relief of thousands of residents in Mbeere region who walk long distances to fetch water in crocodile-infested dams. Ewasco chairman Joel Ngatiari said the company produces and supplies treated water to 170,000 people out of 207,000. Through the expanded treatment plant, company will provide water in all its mandated areas.